<subSubSection lastPageId="2" pageId="1" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1600,2022]" pageId="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1600,1625]" pageId="1">Description.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[456,597,1600,1625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.4" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="9.3" pageId="1" unit="mm" value="9.4" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="9.3">9.3–9.5 mm</quantity>
. Body shape fusiform. Head, pronotum and elytra with coarse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[159,225,1636,1661]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[406,1180,755,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[406,1180,755,1888]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov., male. Scale bar = 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050738/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1600,2022]" pageId="1">
<emphasis box="[199,267,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="1">Head.</emphasis>
Head transverse (
<figureCitation box="[470,538,1672,1697]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) (length 
<quantity box="[641,744,1673,1697]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.9" pageId="1" unit="mm" value="0.89">0.89 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[827,932,1673,1697]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.01" pageId="1" unit="mm" value="1.01">1.01 mm</quantity>
); without evident microsculpture; surface on disc smooth, with simple coarse scattered punctures; without impression, protuberances, or carinae. Eyes prominent, occupying almost two thirds of head length. Neck present (
<figureCitation box="[1025,1102,1744,1769]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Infraorbital carina absent. Coeloconic sensilla absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1600,2022]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,2013]" lastPageId="2" pageId="1">
<emphasis box="[199,337,1816,1841]" italics="true" pageId="1">Mouthparts.</emphasis>
Labrum (
<figureCitation box="[448,515,1816,1841]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) with twelve or more setae on each side; most of setae in anterior half; with more than 30 sensory pores on each side; sensilla on apical margin of epipharynx include anterior or α-sensilla, medial or β-sensilla, posterior or γ-sensilla, and lateral or ε-sensilla, one on each side (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe" box="[1095,1222,1888,1913]" pageId="1" refString="Ashe, J. S. (1984) Generic revision of the subtribe Gyrophaenina (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) with a review of the described subgenera and major features of evolution. Quaestiones Entomologicae, 20, 129 - 349." type="journal article" year="1984">Ashe 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Santiago-Jimenez" pageId="1" refString="Santiago-Jimenez, Q. J. (2010) Revision of the genus Falagonia (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae: Lomechusini), with description of related genera. Sociobiology, 55 (3), 645 - 723." type="journal article" year="2010">Santiago-Jiménez 2010</bibRefCitation>
); apico-medial margin of epipharynx modified into setose or spinose process, one on each side; basal region of epipharynx with five pores in a transverse poorly defined row; medial region of epipharynx with more than 50 pores in an irregular array; mesal region of epipharynx with one &quot;multiporose&quot; sensory structure on each side of midline; with few pores on mesolateral region. Mandibles asymmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[986,1097,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Figs. 3–4</figureCitation>
); right mandible (
<figureCitation box="[1301,1370,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) with medial tooth in dorsal position; left mandible (
<figureCitation box="[673,740,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) without tooth; both mandibles without incisor tooth; without serration between apex and medial tooth on right mandible; with large “velvety patch” area, as wide or wider than half of mandible base, composed of small denticles; prostheca with short hairs along entire length; prosthecal hairs bifurcated in medial area. Maxilla (
<figureCitation box="[547,613,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) with a row of large setae contiguous with the apical spine in apical third of lacinia; with numerous setae in middle third of lacinia; setae present in basal third of lacinia; with pseudopores on cardo. Labium (
<figureCitation box="[364,431,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) with short ligula divided to near base; with small setae on apex of ligula; without medial spines. Prementum with two medial setae, insertions widely separated; medial pseudopore field present; lateral pseudopore field composed of one setose pore, three asetose pores, and around 12 minute pores, without setae on aboral margin of hypoglossa. Mentum without microsculpture and with numerous pores (more than ten pores on each side).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="2">
<emphasis box="[199,288,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="2">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[421,489,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) subquadrate (length 
<quantity box="[736,838,548,572]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.10 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[923,1027,548,572]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.08" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="1.08">1.08 mm</quantity>
); coarsely punctate, punctation does not quite extend to lateral margin; distinctly narrowed behind middle, broadest in anterior half; hypomera not inflexed, visible in lateral view; superior line of hypomera well-defined, in dorsal view completely visible and looking very slightly elevated; anterior angles rounded, posterior angles with distinct, more or less sharp corner; basal fourth of midline with a weak impression, in front of the scutellum. Pronotum with microsetae moderately distributed over the disc, directed posteriorly; with 12 macrosetae, four on each lateral margin, one on each side of midline on apical margin, and one on each side of midline on basal margin; without carina; without microsculpture. Elytron (
<figureCitation box="[254,339,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) longer than wide (length 
<quantity box="[654,760,800,824]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.40 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[849,957,799,824]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="1.05">1.05 mm</quantity>
); surface densely and roughly punctured, interstices quite small, approximately one fourth of the puncture diameter; without microsculpture; with bifurcate carina parallel to external margin; elytral disc with an impression parallel to external margin, next to the internal margin of carina; postero-lateral margin of elytra not sinuate. Elytra with microsetae sparsely distributed, directed posteriorly, with macrosetae distinctly present. Hind wings well developed, with flabellum. Mesocoxal acetabula completely margined posteriorly. Mesocoxal cavities widely separated (
<quantity box="[998,1106,980,1004]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
) by meso- and metaventral processes (
<figureCitation box="[275,357,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); mesoventral process short (
<quantity box="[689,794,1016,1040]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="0.33">0.33 mm</quantity>
) with apex truncated (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1131,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); metaventral process long (1.0 mm), marginate, with apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[643,729,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); isthmus (
<figureCitation box="[862,945,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 17. Structures of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. 2, head, dorsal view; 3, left mandible dorsal view; 4, right mandible, dorsal view; 5, left maxilla, dorsal view; 6, pronotum, dorsal view; 7, prementum and labial palpi, dorsal view; 8, labrum, dorsal view; 9, antenna; 10, right elytra, dorsal view; 11, meso- and metaventrite, ventral view; 12, tergites VII – VIII, dorsal view; 13, sternite VII, showing the external gland (arrows), ventral view; 14, sternites VII – VIII, ventral view; 15, paramere, lateral view; 16, medial lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 17, medial lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050740/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) distinctly present (
<quantity box="[1181,1291,1052,1077]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="0.16">0.16 mm</quantity>
). Legs long, metatarsi with first tarsomere longer than second and third combined; last tarsomere with empodial pad; tarsal claws long and slender, with small basal tooth, and with a single empodial bristle not spatulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="2">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="2">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Abdomen fusiform, glossy, sterna with sparse microsetae to almost glabrous, terga almost glabrous; transverse basal impressions on terga III–VI with sides rounded, directed posteriorly. Abdominal segments III–VI with paratergite and parasternite on each side. Tergite VII with gland opening on anterior margin, and with ctenidia on apical margin. Male with tergite IX divided medially to accommodate tergite X.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1303,1328]" pageId="2">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new genus is the largest 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1821" box="[649,795,1303,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lomechusini">Lomechusini</taxonomicName>
found in 
<collectingRegion box="[904,992,1303,1328]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[904,992,1303,1328]" name="Mexico" pageId="2">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
, close to 
<quantity box="[1098,1154,1304,1328]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
in length. Among all the New World 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1821" box="[289,435,1340,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lomechusini">Lomechusini</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Santiago-Jiménez, 2016" authorityName="Santiago-Jiménez" authorityYear="2016" box="[443,582,1341,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrozoque" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[443,582,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="2">Macrozoque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sharp, 1883)" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1883" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[793,1249,1340,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrogerodonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="godmani">
<emphasis box="[793,1086,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2">Macrogerodonia godmani</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sharp" box="[1102,1241,1340,1365]" pageId="2" refString="Sharp, D. (1883) Fam. Staphylinidae. In: Biologia Centrali-Americana. Insecta, Coleoptera. Vol. 1 (2). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. 145 - 312, pls. 5 - 7." type="book chapter" year="1883">Sharp, 1883</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(described from 
<collectingRegion box="[151,242,1376,1400]" country="Panama" name="Panama" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[151,242,1376,1400]" name="Panama" pageId="2">Panama</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
) with which it shares several characters: 1) a similar body size; 2) a weak impression on the pronotum in front of the scutellum is present, 3) punctation on head, pronotum and elytra is coarse, 4) punctation on pronotum does not extend to the lateral margin, 5) superior line of pronotal hypomeron completely visible from dorsal view and looking very slightly elevated, 6) the first metatarsomere is longer than second and third combined, and 7) abdominal tergite VIII is crenulate. However, the only known species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Santiago-Jiménez, 2016" authorityName="Santiago-Jiménez" authorityYear="2016" box="[962,1101,1521,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrozoque" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[962,1101,1521,1544]" italics="true" pageId="2">Macrozoque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrogerodonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="godmani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2">Macrogerodonia godmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in black body color, while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[558,694,1556,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrogerodonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="godmani">
<emphasis box="[558,581,1557,1580]" italics="true" pageId="2">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[596,694,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="2">godmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is brown. 
<taxonomicName box="[814,1002,1556,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrogerodonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[814,1002,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="2">Macrogerodonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernhauer" box="[1206,1405,1556,1581]" pageId="2" refString="Bernhauer, M. (1941) Staphylinidae (Col.). In: Titschack, E. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Fauna Perus, Band 1. G. Fischer, Jena, pp. 277 - 293." type="book chapter" year="1941">Bernhauer (1941)</bibRefCitation>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1835" box="[312,376,1593,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[312,376,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="2">Zyras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to include one species from 
<collectingCountry box="[699,750,1593,1616]" name="Peru" pageId="2">Peru</collectingCountry>
with pronotal hypomera deflexed, not visible in lateral view. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Santiago-Jiménez, 2016" authorityName="Santiago-Jiménez" authorityYear="2016" box="[187,326,1629,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrozoque" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[187,326,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="2">Macrozoque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the pronotal hypomera are completely visible in lateral view. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authority="Santiago-Jiménez, 2016" authorityName="Santiago-Jiménez" authorityYear="2016" box="[1206,1345,1629,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrozoque" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1206,1345,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="2">Macrozoque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from all the other lomechusines genera based on the following combination of characters: pronotal hypomeron completely visible in lateral view; superior line of pronotal hypomeron completely visible in dorsal view and looking very slightly elevated; pronotum in front of scutellum with weak impression; punctation on head, pronotum and elytra coarse (coarser on pronotum and elytra); punctation on pronotum does not quite extend to the lateral margin; metatarsomere 1 is longer than metatarsomeres 2 and 3 combined; abdominal tergite VIII crenulate; compressor plate of aedeagus is long, almost as long as the median lobe of the aedeagus in dorsal view. Moreover, males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Santiago-Jiménez, 2016" authorityName="Santiago-Jiménez" authorityYear="2016" box="[263,402,1881,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrozoque" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[263,402,1881,1904]" italics="true" pageId="2">Macrozoque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have an external gland on sternite VII, similar to that found in some genera related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Santiago-Jimenez 2010)" authorityName="Santiago-Jimenez" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Santiago-Jimenez" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[151,569,1916,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Falagonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,268,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="2">Falagonia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Santiago-Jimenez" box="[287,562,1916,1941]" pageId="2" refString="Santiago-Jimenez, Q. J. (2010) Revision of the genus Falagonia (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae: Lomechusini), with description of related genera. Sociobiology, 55 (3), 645 - 723." type="journal article" year="2010">Santiago-Jiménez 2010</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The external gland of 
<taxonomicName authority="Santiago-Jiménez, 2016" authorityName="Santiago-Jiménez" authorityYear="2016" box="[854,993,1917,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrozoque" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[854,993,1917,1940]" italics="true" pageId="2">Macrozoque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Santiago-Jimenez (2010)" authorityName="Santiago-Jimenez" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Asheidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1318,1436,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="2">Asheidium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Santiago-Jimenez" box="[151,435,1952,1977]" pageId="2" refString="Santiago-Jimenez, Q. J. (2010) Revision of the genus Falagonia (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae: Lomechusini), with description of related genera. Sociobiology, 55 (3), 645 - 723." type="journal article" year="2010">Santiago-Jiménez (2010)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
