<subSubSection pageId="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="3">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name is formed as a combination of &quot; 
<emphasis box="[896,970,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="3">Macro</emphasis>
-&quot; from Greek &quot; 
<emphasis box="[1149,1230,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3">makros</emphasis>
&quot; (meaning large), and &quot;Zoque&quot;, the name of the indigenous ethnic population inhabiting the Chimalapas forest in 
<collectingRegion box="[1220,1309,188,213]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="3">
<collectingCountry box="[1220,1309,188,213]" name="Mexico" pageId="3">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" box="[199,383,223,248]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,223,248]" pageId="3">Gender.</emphasis>
Neuter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,970,260,285]" pageId="3" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" box="[199,970,260,285]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,260,285]" pageId="3">Habitat.</emphasis>
Unknown. Material was collected with flight intercept trap.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,295,320]" pageId="3">Distribution.</emphasis>
The single described species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santiago-Jiménez" authorityYear="2016" box="[694,1012,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Macrozoque" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoplandrioides">
<emphasis box="[694,1012,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="3">Macrozoque hoplandrioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is known only from the Chimalapas region in 
<collectingRegion box="[258,345,332,356]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="3">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[356,441,332,357]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="3">
<collectingCountry box="[356,441,332,357]" name="Mexico" pageId="3">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[457,540,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1259,1281]" captionTargetBox="[282,1306,197,1235]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[276,1310,193,1237]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 18. Collection site of Macrozoque hoplandrioides gen. nov. and sp. nov. (black circle)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050742/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
